<DocsLayout title="Douto" description="Local doctrine pipeline and internal doctrinal artifact supplier for Valter.">
  <h1>Douto</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Local doctrine pipeline</p>

  <span class="badge badge-dev">dev</span>

  <p>
    Douto is not presented here as an end-user product. Today it is
    a local doctrine pipeline with CLI search, a curated corpus, and an editorial
    markdown layer built to produce reusable artifacts for the rest of the ecosystem.
  </p>

  <p>
    Its primary consumer is <strong>Valter</strong>. The priority is to build a
    reproducible, auditable pipeline for contracts and civil procedure, with quality
    gates and controlled handoff, before any "doctrine assistant" narrative for
    end users.
  </p>

  <h2>Role in the ecosystem</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Internal doctrinal artifact supplier for Valter</li>
    <li>Curated corpus with initial focus on contracts and civil procedure</li>
    <li>Local and editorial workflow, not a standalone web experience</li>
    <li>Precision and reproducibility ahead of delivery speed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Stack</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Language:</strong> Python 3</li>
    <li><strong>Operation:</strong> local CLI</li>
    <li><strong>PDF extraction:</strong> LlamaParse</li>
    <li><strong>Enrichment:</strong> MiniMax M2.5</li>
    <li><strong>Embeddings:</strong> Legal-BERTimbau (768-dim)</li>
    <li><strong>Editorial base:</strong> Markdown + Obsidian conventions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Current priorities</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Reproducible foundation for the pipeline and local paths</li>
    <li>Quality gate for contracts and civil procedure</li>
    <li>Artifact contract for handoff into Valter</li>
    <li>Explainable retrieval and synthesis only after the previous gates</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Links</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://douto.sens.legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Documentation</a></li>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/sensdiego/douto" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>

